- **Latest Version**: Spring Cloud Stream Kafka Transaction Guide as of October 2025.
- **Key Config Options**:
  - `spring.cloud.stream.kafka.binder.transaction.id-prefix`: Prefix for the transaction ID to avoid conflicts.
  - `spring.cloud.stream.bindings.output.producer.transactional-id`: Specifies the transactional ID for the producer.
- **CLI Commands**: Not applicable directly, but ensure your project dependencies are up-to-date and include necessary Spring Cloud Stream Kafka libraries.
- **Example Code Snippet**:
  ```java
  @EnableBinding(Sink.class)
  public class TransactionalKafkaProducer {

      @Autowired
      private MessageChannel output;

      @Transactional
      public void sendMessage(String message) {
          output.send(MessageBuilder.withPayload(message).build());
      }
  }
  ```
- **Documentation**: Refer to the [Spring Cloud Stream Kafka Transaction Guide](https://spring.io/blog/2025/10/14/spring-cloud-stream-kafka-transactions) for detailed setup and usage instructions.
